The paper discusses query optimization and resource allocation in big data systems, which are typically implemented using distributed databases and parallel computing techniques. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the challenges of running big data systems on cloud environments, which involves distributed computing and resource management, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely categories as well. The paper also proposes new optimization techniques and algorithms, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
